urn a _valid_ answer, and <br />should do so.<br /><br />Without DEBUG_SPINLOCK, there isn't any answer to return.<br /><br />So there's no way we can or should be consistent. In one case an answer <br />exists, in another one the answer is meaningless and doesn't exist.<br /><br />&gt; How much of this do we want to try and address in .31?<br /><br />Absolutely nothing.<br /><br />&gt; The PPC test really should be using assert_spin_locked and I'll send a patch<br />&gt; to Ben for that.<br /><br />Yes, that's the correct fix.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
